# Shadcn-UI Implementation with ViewComponents

## **Overview**

We implement Shadcn-UI patterns using our existing **ViewComponent + TailwindCSS** architecture, maintaining our HTML-over-JavaScript approach while providing the same developer experience and visual consistency as Shadcn-UI.

## **✅ Current Shadcn-UI Equivalent Components**

We already have most Shadcn-UI components implemented:

- **Button** → `DS::Button` (with variants: primary, secondary, destructive, outline, ghost, icon)
- **Dialog** → `DS::Dialog` (modal/drawer variants with auto-open, slots)
- **Disclosure/Collapsible** → `DS::Disclosure` (native `<details>` element)
- **Tabs** → `DS::Tabs` (with URL params and session persistence)
- **Menu/Dropdown** → `DS::Menu` (with variants: icon, button, avatar)
- **Toggle/Switch** → `DS::Toggle` (native checkbox with custom styling)
- **Tooltip** → `DS::Tooltip` (using @floating-ui/dom)
- **Alert** → `DS::Alert`
- **Link** → `DS::Link` (extends DS::Button variants)

## **🎯 Implementation Strategy**

### **1. Design System Architecture**

```ruby
# Base component structure (already implemented)
class DS::ComponentName < DesignSystemComponent
  VARIANTS = {
    default: { container_classes: "...", icon_classes: "..." },
    secondary: { container_classes: "...", icon_classes: "..." }
  }.freeze
  
  SIZES = {
    sm: { container_classes: "...", text_classes: "..." },
    md: { container_classes: "...", text_classes: "..." }
  }.freeze
end
```

### **2. Design Token System**

Our design tokens in `app/assets/tailwind/maybe-design-system.css` provide Shadcn-UI equivalent functionality:

```css
/* Functional tokens (Shadcn-UI equivalent) */
@utility text-primary { /* --foreground */ }
@utility text-secondary { /* --muted-foreground */ }
@utility bg-container { /* --background */ }
@utility bg-surface { /* --card */ }
@utility border-primary { /* --border */ }
```

### **3. Component Patterns**

**✅ DO: Use our ViewComponent patterns**
```erb
<!-- Shadcn-UI style usage -->
<%= render DS::Button.new(variant: "outline", size: "sm") do %>
  Click me
<% end %>

<!-- With slots (like Shadcn-UI compound components) -->
<%= render DS::Dialog.new(variant: "modal") do |dialog| %>
  <% dialog.with_header(title: "Settings") %>
  <% dialog.with_body do %>
    <!-- Content -->
  <% end %>
  <% dialog.with_actions do %>
    <%= render DS::Button.new(variant: "primary", text: "Save") %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
```

**❌ DON'T: Try to install React Shadcn-UI**
```bash
# This conflicts with our HTML-over-JavaScript approach
npx shadcn-ui@latest init
```

