## **📋 Implementation Guidelines**

### **Component Structure**

```ruby
class DS::NewComponent < DesignSystemComponent
  # 1. Define variants (like Shadcn-UI)
  VARIANTS = {
    default: { container_classes: "bg-container border border-primary" },
    destructive: { container_classes: "bg-red-50 border border-red-200" }
  }.freeze
  
  # 2. Define sizes
  SIZES = {
    sm: { container_classes: "p-2 text-sm" },
    md: { container_classes: "p-4 text-base" }
  }.freeze
  
  # 3. Use slots for compound components
  renders_one :header
  renders_one :body
  renders_many :actions
  
  # 4. Initialize with Shadcn-UI style API
  def initialize(variant: :default, size: :md, **opts)
    @variant = variant.to_sym
    @size = size.to_sym
    @opts = opts
  end
end
```

### **Template Structure**

```erb
<!-- Use semantic HTML with design tokens -->
<div class="<%= container_classes %>" <%= html_attributes %>>
  <% if header? %>
    <header class="border-b border-primary pb-2">
      <%= header %>
    </header>
  <% end %>
  
  <% if body? %>
    <div class="py-2">
      <%= body %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
  
  <%= content %>
end
```

### **Progressive Enhancement**

```javascript
// Minimal Stimulus controller for interactivity
import { Controller } from "@hotwired/stimulus"

export default class extends Controller {
  static targets = ["content"]
  
  toggle() {
    this.contentTarget.classList.toggle("hidden")
  }
}
```

## **🎨 Design Token Extensions**

Add Shadcn-UI equivalent tokens to `maybe-design-system.css`:

```css
/* Card/Surface tokens */
@utility bg-card {
  @apply bg-white;
  @variant theme-dark {
    @apply bg-gray-800;
  }
}

/* Muted backgrounds */
@utility bg-muted {
  @apply bg-gray-50;
  @variant theme-dark {
    @apply bg-gray-900;
  }
}

/* Accent colors */
@utility bg-accent {
  @apply bg-gray-100;
  @variant theme-dark {
    @apply bg-gray-700;
  }
}
```

## **📦 Component Generator**

Create a Rails generator for new DS components:

```bash
# Generate new component with Shadcn-UI patterns
rails generate ds_component Card variant:default,outline size:sm,md,lg
```

## **🧪 Testing Strategy**

```ruby
# Component preview (like Storybook)
class CardComponentPreview < ViewComponent::Preview
  def default
    render DS::Card.new(variant: "default") do |card|
      card.with_header { "Card Title" }
      card.with_body { "Card content goes here" }
    end
  end
end

# Unit tests
class DS::CardTest < ViewComponent::TestCase
  def test_renders_with_variants
    render_inline DS::Card.new(variant: "outline")
    assert_selector "div.border-primary"
  nend
end
```

## **🔄 Migration from Hardcoded Styles**

### **Before (Hardcoded)**
```erb
<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
  <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Title</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600">Content</p>
</div>
```

### **After (Component + Design Tokens)**
```erb
<%= render DS::Card.new do |card| %>
  <% card.with_header { "Title" } %>
  <% card.with_body { "Content" } %>
<% end %>
```

